{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThree low-severity test-quality issues from the validation are worth cleaning up:\n\n- The post-deletion smoke test\n  (`tests/integration/rebar_reconciler/test_post_deletion_smoke.py`) invokes each leaf\n  but catches/ignores every exception except `ModuleNotFoundError` and asserts only that\n  the registry has `>=6` entries — it is linkage coverage but is named/positioned as if\n  it proves every leaf is invocable.\n- `test_repair_json_receives_schema` only asserts the schema object is forwarded as a\n  kwarg; it never shows schema guidance changes a parsed result.\n- `test_capture_baseline_not_implemented_error_not_raised` asserts only `is not None`,\n  duplicating stronger neighboring baseline tests.\n\n## What\n\n- Rename/rescope the smoke test to what it actually proves, add a behavioral\n  schema-guided parse test, and remove/fold the redundant baseline test.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `tests/integration/rebar_reconciler/test_post_deletion_smoke.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_silent_success.py`\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/orchestrate/test_health_baseline.py`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The post-deletion smoke test is renamed to reflect stale-import/linkage detection\n      and its docstring/coverage note scopes it to linkage only (prefer importing/\n      resolving referenced modules over pretend-executing every leaf).\n- [ ] A new behavioral test pins schema-guided parsing with a CONCRETE, committed\n      fixture: schema\n      `{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"count\":{\"type\":\"integer\"}},\"required\":[\"count\"]}`\n      (or the equivalent Pydantic model), malformed/ambiguous payload `'{\"count\": \"3\"}'`,\n      expected validated object `count == 3` (int). The primary, version-stable assertion\n      is that `parse_structured(<model>, payload)` returns the coerced model\n      (`count=3:int`) while `tolerant_parse(payload)` with NO schema returns\n      `{\"count\": \"3\"}` (string) — a deterministic, installed-library-independent\n      difference. IF a payload is also found for which `json_repair.repair_json(schema=)`\n      itself differs from the schema-less call on the installed version, assert that too;\n      otherwise the AC is satisfied by the `parse_structured` coercion assertion and the\n      finding is noted in the test. The forwarding spy is kept only as a narrow\n      integration check.\n- [ ] `test_capture_baseline_not_implemented_error_not_raised` is deleted or folded into\n      the strongest baseline test.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783889505017380001,"uuid":"01b2c1f2-412c-43f2-9851-25d07cdf86a9"}